United States

  • Territory: includes 50 total states (48 continental, Hawaii, and Alaska)
  • Total Population: 328.2 million (2019)
  • Government: Representative Democracy (at both state and federal levels)

China

  • Territory: 22 provinces* governed by the People's Republic of China, 4 municipalities, 5 autonomous regions, and 2 special administrative regions
    *The People's Republic of China claims 23 provinces total, but Taiwan is officially the Republic of China rather than a province.
  • Total Population: 1.398 billion (2019)
  • Government: Chinese Communist Party (divided into legislative, executive, military, supervisory, judicial, and procuratorial branches)

Russia

  • Territory: 85 federal subjects (of which 22 are republics)
  • Total Population: 146.962 million (2020)
  • Government: Federal Multiparty Republic

Belgium

  • Territory: 3 regions (further divided into 10 provinces)
  • Total Population: 11.46 million (2019)
  • Government: Constitutional Monarchy with a Representative Democracy

Vatican City

  • Territory: No administrative divisions
  • Total Population: 825 (2019)
  • Government: Theocratic Absolute Elective Monarchy

Bermuda

  • Territory: 9 parishes
  • Total Population: 63,918 (2019)
  • Government: Self-governing British territory

Democratic People's Republic of Korea

  • Territory: 9 provinces
  • Total Population: 25.67 million (2019)
  • Government: Dictatorship

Uganda

  • Territory: 135 districts
  • Total Population: 44.27 million (2019)
  • Government: Presidential Republic
